# Firebase Configuration Template

Copy this file, rename to `.env`, and fill in your actual Firebase credentials:

```
PORT=5001
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here_change_this_in_production
NODE_ENV=development
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYourPrivateKeyHere\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxx@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com
```

**Or use firebase-key.json approach:**

```
PORT=5001
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_here_change_this_in_production
NODE_ENV=development
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./firebase-key.json
```

## How to Get Firebase Credentials:

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Select your project
3. Click ⚙️ (Settings) → Project Settings
4. Go to "Service Accounts" tab
5. Click "Generate New Private Key"
6. Save the JSON file as `firebase-key.json` in the backend root directory

**IMPORTANT:** Add `firebase-key.json` to `.gitignore` to keep credentials secure!
